Syntax: attribute <personal | condition | stats>

The attribute command will displays extended information about
your character.  Please note that some of the extended information
is restricted to characters over a given level.

The personal section lists basic information about your person.  Age,
background, allegiance, etc. is contained herein.

The condition section displays information of a more transitory
nature.  Spells in effect, major limb damage, current characteristics,
position, etc are all contained in this section.  The primary bonuses
or penalties you get from the majority of your characteristics will
also be displayed if you are of high enough level.

The stats section is used to keep track of career and session information
and is used mostly as bragging rights.

See also:  SCORE
Related Topics: GENERAL INFO
